# IBEX Harness — Root Cursor Rules
# Production-grade AI agent memory and context management platform
# Target: Fortune 500 / MAANG-acceptable code quality

## MANDATORY: Read before any task
Before generating any code, always read and apply the rules from
.cursor/rules/ that match the file type and task at hand.

## Rule registry
00-project-overview.mdc        → Always applied. Project context, service map, naming conventions.
01-go-code-quality.mdc         → All *.go files outside test files.
02-go-error-handling.mdc       → All *.go files.
03-go-concurrency.mdc          → All *.go files that use goroutines, channels, sync primitives.
04-go-testing.mdc              → All *_test.go files.
05-go-performance.mdc          → All *.go files in hot paths (proxy, auth, ratelimit, context).
06-go-grpc-protobuf.mdc        → *.proto files and gRPC handler/client code.
07-python-code-quality.mdc     → All *.py files.
08-python-fastapi.mdc          → *.py files in services/api/, services/memory/, services/context/.
09-python-testing.mdc          → test_*.py and *_test.py files.
10-python-async.mdc            → *.py files using asyncio, Celery, aiohttp.
11-typescript-react.mdc        → *.ts, *.tsx files in services/dashboard/.
12-typescript-testing.mdc      → *.test.ts, *.spec.ts, *.test.tsx files.
13-sql-postgres.mdc            → *.sql files, Go files with SQL queries, Python SQLAlchemy.
14-sql-migrations.mdc          → infra/migrations/**/*.sql files.
15-redis-patterns.mdc          → Any code that calls Redis (Go, Python).
16-docker.mdc                  → Dockerfile*, docker-compose*.yml files.
17-security.mdc                → Always applied. Security is non-negotiable across all files.
18-observability.mdc           → Always applied. Logging/metrics/tracing in all services.
19-api-design.mdc              → HTTP handler files, proto definitions, OpenAPI specs.
20-architecture-layering.mdc   → Always applied. Layer boundaries enforced everywhere.
21-complexity-management.mdc   → Always applied. CodeScene complexity gates.
22-data-structures-algorithms.mdc → Algorithm selection and data structure choices.
23-testing-strategy.mdc        → Always applied. Test quality and coverage requirements.
24-config-management.mdc       → Config loading files, env vars, any os.Getenv call.
25-ci-cd-pipeline.mdc          → .github/workflows/*.yml, Makefile, scripts/*.sh.
26-pr-git-workflow.mdc         → PR descriptions, commit messages, branch names.
27-milestone-writing.mdc       → docs/roadmap/**/*.md files.
28-multitenant-security.mdc    → Always applied. Every DB query, every handler, every cache key.
29-ibex-packages.mdc           → Always applied. Package usage rules for shared packages.
pr-template.mdc                → Always applied. Full GitHub PR template sections (repo-specific).
testing-verification.mdc       → Always applied. Local test/gofmt/repo-guards before push.

## The one rule above all rules
"Would a principal engineer at Stripe, Google, or AWS accept this in code review?"
If the honest answer is no, do not write it.
